<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ædas" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>ædas</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>безопасный</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>safe</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>ædas ran næ bacagūryn qæwy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>нам надо разыскать безопасное место</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>we need to find a safe place</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>jæ mūlk ædas ū</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в безопасности имение его</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>his goods are in peace</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i11%i 21</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>læppū kæfq˳yndary k˳y amardta, wæd donʒawtæ ædasæj cæwyn bajdydtoj donmæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>когда юноша убил дракона, водоносы стали в безопасности ходить за водой</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>when the young man killed the dragon, the water carriers began to walk safely for water</q></cit></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>ædas ran næ bacagūryn qæwy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>нам надо разыскать безопасное место</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>we need to find a safe place</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>jæ mūlk ædas ū</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в безопасности имение его</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>his goods are in peace</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i11%i 21</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>læppū kæfq˳yndary k˳y amardta, wæd donʒawtæ ædasæj cæwyn bajdydtoj donmæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>когда юноша убил дракона, водоносы стали в безопасности ходить за водой</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>when the young man killed the dragon, the water carriers began to walk safely for water</q></cit></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æ-"/> (негативная частица) + <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/> ‘страх’, ‘опасность’. Старая форма %i*ætas%i сохранена в <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>Ἀτάσας</w></mentioned> — собственное имя, имевшее, вероятно, значение „бесстрашный“ (<bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author><ref target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1886, окт., стр. 263</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1886, oct., p. 263</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Vasmer._Ir._i._S."/></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>151</biblScope></bibl>). См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æ-"/> (negative particle) + <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/> ‘fear’, ‘danger’. The old form %i*ætas%i is preserved in <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>Ἀτάσας</w></mentioned> , proper name, which probably had the meaning “fearless” (<bibl><author>Vs. Miller</author><ref target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1886, окт., стр. 263</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1886, oct., p. 263</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Vasmer._Ir._i._S."/></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>151</biblScope></bibl>). See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/>.</etym></entry>